Nate Ledbetter <ltdomer98@...> wrote:

--- Rod Pavez <grfkboyz@...> wrote:

> Hi there everybody:
> There is a type of toy like a puzzle that originated
> in Japan. The 
> pieces are made of metal or ceramic and triangular
> shaped, usually 
> they are black or some dark color. Children
> entertain themselves by 
> making shapes with them.
> Do any of you know the name of this? If you have any
> information on it 
> please let me know. Thanks.
> By the way love the Samurai Moderators homepage.
> Sweet.
> Later 


As a kid I always called them "Tangrams", that's the
name they were sold under in the US. Last week there
was a set in a hotel I stayed at on Lake Biwa, but I
don't remember it having any particular name.
